
------------------------------------------------------------------
INSTALLATION NOTES for ELLE
------------------------------------------------------------------

UNIX systems

In the following steps, replace /usr/local with the directory in which
you decide to install the package.

1)  elle.tar.gz (or elle.tgz)
    Extract the file in an appropriate directory, usually /usr/local.
      tar xzf elle.tar.gz 

    elle.tar.Z
    Uncompress and untar the elle.tar.Z file in an appropriate directory,
    usually /usr/local.
      uncompress elle.tar.Z
      tar xvf elle.tar
    or
      zcat elle.tar.Z | tar xvf -

2) change to the directory /usr/local/elle/elle and run
     ./install.sh help
   and follow the instructions to build the versions you need.
   To compile the WX programs, you must have wxWidgets libraries
   installed (www.wxwidgets.org)
   This script uses xmkmf, imake and the configuration files in
   the X11 configuration directory (eg /usr/X11R6/lib/config)

CYGWIN

1) as above

2) change to the directory /usr/local/elle/elle and run
     ./install.win wx
